snippet: Gunmen stormed an apartment complex known for prostitution and killed at least 20 women and six men, according to the Interior Ministry.
abstract: Iraqi militants kill at least 26 people in raid on Baghdad building known for prostitution; attack adds to chaos sweeping the country.

byline.contributor: Omar Jawoshy contributed reporting from Iraq, and Iraqi employees of The New York Times from Diyala and Kirkuk Provinces.

lead_paragraph: Gunmen stormed an apartment complex known for prostitution and killed at least 20 women and six men, according to the Interior Ministry.

headline.main: Iraqi Militants Kill 26 in Raid on Baghdad Building
headline.print_headline: Iraqi Militants Kill 26 in Raid on Baghdad Building
